pageContext.description: Dimensions: EL 99.3mm; Wbl 44.5mm; EDs 56.0mm; Ts (at break) 1.5-2.0,Typology: thin rib in crest of midrib of loz. section; half hollow blade wings - very little taper, markedly concave edge bevel,Manufacture: strictions along blade - anc. grmks. or mod.? small dents on one wing - manu. or dam.?,Condition: most of edge little irregular but close to original line - patina flaking; much of main fracture looks anc. - a little poss recent; dents along midrib prob. anc.
pageContext.surface: Most retaining dull green patina - areas becoming pocked; edges and part of midrib crest flaked to dry pale grey green surface
pageContext.collection: London, Society of Antiquaries Collection, B49 (v)
pageContext.site: Unprovenanced,Alt Site: Shropshire, Little Wenlock, Willowmoor, c. SJ 6403 0830,Provenance not recorded, probably from the Willow Moor Hoard (see AFI)
